1. Pre-Requisites (What You Need)

Before starting, ensure you have the following items ready:

A Gmail Account: A valid Google email ID.
Debit or Credit Card:
Visa and Mastercard are accepted. RuPay cards are generally NOT accepted.
You need a card that supports international/online transactions (RBI guidelines in India).
You will be charged a small verification amount (typically ₹2 or $1), which is immediately refunded.

2. What You Get (Free Tier Benefits)

When you create a trial account, you receive:

$300 Credits: Valid for 90 Days (previously 12 months, but recently changed to 3 months).
Auto-Expiry: Credits automatically expire after 90 days. Unused credits don't roll over.
No Auto-Charge: Google explicitly states, "Not to charge after free trial ends." You are only charged if you manually click the "Activate" button to upgrade to a paid account.
Free Products: Access to 20+ products with monthly usage limits (e.g., 1 Compute Engine f1-micro instance per month, 1TB Cloud Storage).


Verification Charge:

You will receive an OTP from your bank to authorize the transaction. Enter it to verify.
Survey: Fill out the quick survey about your role/interest (e.g., Student, Learning about Cloud) and click "Done".

