Crucial Warning: The console shows an "Activate" button (to switch to a full paid account). Never click this unless you want to be charged. Just click "Dismiss" or ignore it.
OTP Auto-Debit Message: After creation, your bank might send an SMS saying "Auto-debit activated for up to ₹75,000/₹1,50,000 for Google Cloud." Do not panic. This is just a maximum upper limit for safety; Google will not charge you unless you manually upgrade the account.

5. Troubleshooting Tips
Card Declined: This can happen randomly. Try a different card, or wait 24 hours and try again. Even with valid cards, Google sometimes rejects on the first attempt.

Unregistered Failure: If the account creation fails while selecting "Unregistered Individual," retry by selecting "Registered" and entering your PAN number. It validates the identity better.
